H0.text: Cells -> organs -> organ system -> tissue is the series that correctly represents the levels of organization in an organism.

H1.text: Cells → tissue → organs → organ system is the correct series that represents the levels of organization in an organism.

H2.text: Tissue → cells → organ system → organs is the series that correctly represents the levels of organization in an organism.

H3.text: Tissue -> organ system -> cells -> organs is the series that correctly represents the levels of organization in an organism.

A4.text: Organs are formed by the functional grouping together of two or more different tissue types.

A5.text: Simple permanent tissue is a group of cells that are similar in origin, structure, and function.
